description: From Middle French macule, from Latin macula. Doublet of maquis.

entries.meaning: A blur or an appearance of a double impression, as when the paper slips a little during printing.

verbs.description: macule (third-person singular simple present macules, present participle maculing, simple past and past participle maculed)

entries.meaning: (printing) To blur or be blurred; especially to blur or double an impression from type.
